<P>
Customers of Southern California Edison will see a 3.3% increase in their 
monthly electric bills starting Feb. 1, under an order issued in San Francisco 
by the state Public Utilities Commission. 
</P>
<P>
The order will increase the typical residential customer's winter bill to 
$54.75 per month from $52.98. The typical monthly bill for summer will rise to 
$55.24 from $53.51. The rate hike will add $59.6 million to Edison's annual 
revenues. 
</P>
